#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.65"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.65:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.65:0.2"
msgid "7. Mahāvagga "
msgstr "7. The Great Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.65:0.3"
msgid "65. Kesamuttisutta "
msgstr "65. With the Kālāmas of Kesamutta "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an3.65:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
#. VAR: kesamuttaṃ → kesaputtaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.65:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ yena kesamuttaṃ nāma kālāmānaṃ nigamo tadavasari. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kosalans together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants when he arrived at a town of the Kālāmas named Kesamutta. "

msgctxt "an3.65:1.3"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho kesamuttiyā kālāmā: "
msgstr "The Kālāmas of Kesamutta heard: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.65:1.4"
msgid "“samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito kesamuttaṃ anuppatto. "
msgstr "“It seems the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—has arrived at Kesamutta. "

msgctxt "an3.65:1.5"
msgid "Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato: "
msgstr "He has this good reputation: "

msgctxt "an3.65:1.6"
msgid "‘itipi so bhagavā … pe … "
msgstr "‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha …’ "

msgctxt "an3.65:1.7"
msgid "sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī’”ti. "
msgstr "It’s good to see such perfected ones.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an3.65:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho kesamuttiyā kālāmā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā appekacce bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu, appekacce bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu, appekacce yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu, appekacce nāmagottaṃ sāvetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu, appekacce tuṇhībhūtā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te kesamuttiyā kālāmā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then the Kālāmas went up to the Buddha. Before sitting down to one side, some bowed, some exchanged greetings and polite conversation, some held up their joined palms toward the Buddha, some announced their name and clan, while some kept silent. Seated to one side the Kālāmas said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.189, sc3
msgctxt "an3.65:3.1"
msgid "“Santi, bhante, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kesamuttaṃ āgacchanti. "
msgstr "“There are, sir, some ascetics and brahmins who come to Kesamutta. "

#. VAR: parappavādaṃ → paravādaṃ (bj, s1-3)
#. VAR: paribhavanti omakkhiṃ → opapakkhiṃ (sī, syā1-3, kaṃ, pā1), omakkhikaṃ (ka-ma)
msgctxt "an3.65:3.2"
msgid "Te sakaṃyeva vādaṃ dīpenti jotenti, parappavādaṃ pana khuṃsenti vambhenti paribhavanti omakkhiṃ karonti. "
msgstr "They explain and promote only their own doctrine, while they attack, badmouth, disparage, and smear the doctrines of others. "

msgctxt "an3.65:3.3"
msgid "Aparepi, bhante, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kesamuttaṃ āgacchanti. "
msgstr "Then some other ascetics and brahmins come to Kesamutta. "

msgctxt "an3.65:3.4"
msgid "Tepi sakaṃyeva vādaṃ dīpenti jotenti, parappavādaṃ pana khuṃsenti vambhenti paribhavanti omakkhiṃ karonti. "
msgstr "They too explain and promote only their own doctrine, while they attack, badmouth, disparage, and smear the doctrines of others. "

msgctxt "an3.65:3.5"
msgid "Tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ hoteva kaṅkhā hoti vicikicchā: "
msgstr "So, sir, we’re doubting and uncertain: "

msgctxt "an3.65:3.6"
msgid "‘ko su nāma imesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ āha, ko musā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘I wonder who of these respected ascetics and brahmins speaks the truth, and who speaks falsehood?’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.65:3.7"
msgid "“Alañhi vo, kālāmā, kaṅkhituṃ alaṃ vicikicchituṃ. "
msgstr "“It is enough, Kālāmas, for you to be doubting and uncertain. "

#. VAR: Kaṅkhanīyeva pana → kaṅkhanīye ca pana (bj) | kaṅkhāniyeva pana (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.65:3.8"
msgid "Kaṅkhanīyeva pana vo ṭhāne vicikicchā uppannā. "
msgstr "Doubt has come up in you about an uncertain matter. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an3.65:4.1"
msgid "Etha tumhe, kālāmā, mā anussavena, mā paramparāya, mā itikirāya, mā piṭakasampadānena, mā takkahetu, mā nayahetu, mā ākāraparivitakkena, mā diṭṭhinijjhānakkhantiyā, mā bhabbarūpatāya, mā samaṇo no garūti. "
msgstr "Please, Kālāmas, don’t go by oral transmission, don’t go by lineage, don’t go by testament, don’t go by canonical authority, don’t rely on logic, don’t rely on inference, don’t go by reasoned contemplation, don’t go by the acceptance of a view after consideration, don’t go by the appearance of competence, and don’t think ‘The ascetic is our respected teacher.’ "

msgctxt "an3.65:4.2"
msgid "Yadā tumhe, kālāmā, attanāva jāneyyātha: "
msgstr "But when you know for yourselves: "

#. VAR: samādinnā → samādiṇṇā (mr)
msgctxt "an3.65:4.3"
msgid "‘ime dhammā akusalā, ime dhammā sāvajjā, ime dhammā viññugarahitā, ime dhammā samattā samādinnā ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattantī’ti, atha tumhe, kālāmā, pajaheyyātha. "
msgstr "‘These things are unskillful, blameworthy, criticized by sensible people, and when you undertake them, they lead to harm and suffering’, then you should give them up. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an3.65:5.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, kālāmā, "
msgstr "What do you think, Kālāmas? "

msgctxt "an3.65:5.2"
msgid "lobho purisassa ajjhattaṃ uppajjamāno uppajjati hitāya vā ahitāya vā”ti? "
msgstr "Does greed come up in a person for their welfare or harm?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an3.65:6.1"
msgid "“Ahitāya, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Harm, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
#. VAR: tathattāya → tadatthāya (mr)
#. VAR: yaṃ sa → yaṃ tassa (mr)
msgctxt "an3.65:7.1"
msgid "“Luddho panāyaṃ, kālāmā, purisapuggalo lobhena abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto pāṇampi hanati, adinnampi ādiyati, paradārampi gacchati, musāpi bhaṇati, parampi tathattāya samādapeti, yaṃ sa hoti dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti. "
msgstr "“A greedy individual, overcome by greed, kills living creatures, steals, commits adultery, lies, and encourages others to do the same. Is that for their lasting harm and suffering?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an3.65:8.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an3.65:9.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, kālāmā, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Kālāmas? "

msgctxt "an3.65:9.2"
msgid "doso purisassa ajjhattaṃ uppajjamāno uppajjati hitāya vā ahitāya vā”ti? "
msgstr "Does hate come up in a person for their welfare or harm?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an3.65:10.1"
msgid "“Ahitāya, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Harm, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
#. VAR: hanati → hanti (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.65:11.1"
msgid "“Duṭṭho panāyaṃ, kālāmā, purisapuggalo dosena abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto pāṇampi hanati, adinnampi ādiyati, paradārampi gacchati, musāpi bhaṇati, parampi tathattāya samādapeti, yaṃ sa hoti dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti. "
msgstr "“A hateful individual, overcome by hate, kills living creatures, steals, commits adultery, lies, and encourages others to do the same. Is that for their lasting harm and suffering?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an3.65:12.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "an3.65:13.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, kālāmā, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Kālāmas? "

msgctxt "an3.65:13.2"
msgid "moho purisassa ajjhattaṃ uppajjamāno uppajjati hitāya vā ahitāya vā”ti? "
msgstr "Does delusion come up in a person for their welfare or harm?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "an3.65:14.1"
msgid "“Ahitāya, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Harm, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.190, sc15
msgctxt "an3.65:15.1"
msgid "“Mūḷho panāyaṃ, kālāmā, purisapuggalo mohena abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto pāṇampi hanati, adinnampi ādiyati, paradārampi gacchati, musāpi bhaṇati, parampi tathattāya samādapeti, yaṃ sa hoti dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti. "
msgstr "“A deluded individual, overcome by delusion, kills living creatures, steals, commits adultery, lies, and encourages others to do the same. Is that for their lasting harm and suffering?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "an3.65:16.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "an3.65:17.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, kālāmā, ime dhammā kusalā vā akusalā vā”ti? "
msgstr "“What do you think, Kālāmas, are these things skillful or unskillful?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "an3.65:18.1"
msgid "“Akusalā, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Unskillful, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "an3.65:19.1"
msgid "“Sāvajjā vā anavajjā vā”ti? "
msgstr "“Blameworthy or blameless?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "an3.65:20.1"
msgid "“Sāvajjā, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Blameworthy, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "an3.65:21.1"
msgid "“Viññugarahitā vā viññuppasatthā vā”ti? "
msgstr "“Criticized or praised by sensible people?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22
msgctxt "an3.65:22.1"
msgid "“Viññugarahitā, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Criticized by sensible people, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "an3.65:23.1"
msgid "“Samattā samādinnā ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattanti, no vā? "
msgstr "“When you undertake them, do they lead to harm and suffering, or not? "

#. VAR: Kathaṃ vā → kathaṃ vā vo (?)
msgctxt "an3.65:23.2"
msgid "Kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti? "
msgstr "Or how do you see this?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc24
msgctxt "an3.65:24.1"
msgid "“Samattā, bhante, samādinnā ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattantīti. "
msgstr "“When you undertake them, they lead to harm and suffering. "

msgctxt "an3.65:24.2"
msgid "Evaṃ no ettha hotī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how we see it.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc25
#. VAR: avocumhā → avocumha (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.65:25.1"
msgid "“Iti kho, kālāmā, yaṃ taṃ avocumhā: "
msgstr "“So, Kālāmas, when I said: "

msgctxt "an3.65:25.2"
msgid "‘etha tumhe, kālāmā. "
msgstr "‘Please, "

msgctxt "an3.65:25.3"
msgid "Mā anussavena, mā paramparāya, mā itikirāya, mā piṭakasampadānena, mā takkahetu, mā nayahetu, mā ākāraparivitakkena, mā diṭṭhinijjhānakkhantiyā, mā bhabbarūpatāya, mā samaṇo no garūti. "
msgstr "don’t go by oral transmission, don’t go by lineage, don’t go by testament, don’t go by canonical authority, don’t rely on logic, don’t rely on inference, don’t go by reasoned contemplation, don’t go by the acceptance of a view after consideration, don’t go by the appearance of competence, and don’t think “The ascetic is our respected teacher.” "

msgctxt "an3.65:25.4"
msgid "Yadā tumhe kālāmā attanāva jāneyyātha: "
msgstr "But when you know for yourselves: "

msgctxt "an3.65:25.5"
msgid "“ime dhammā akusalā, ime dhammā sāvajjā, ime dhammā viññugarahitā, ime dhammā samattā samādinnā ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattantīti, atha tumhe, kālāmā, pajaheyyāthā”’ti, "
