msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc26
msgctxt "an3.65:26.1"
msgid "Etha tumhe, kālāmā, mā anussavena, mā paramparāya, mā itikirāya, mā piṭakasampadānena, mā takkahetu, mā nayahetu, mā ākāraparivitakkena, mā diṭṭhinijjhānakkhantiyā, mā bhabbarūpatāya, mā samaṇo no garūti. "
msgstr "Please, Kālāmas, don’t go by oral transmission, don’t go by lineage, don’t go by testament, don’t go by canonical authority, don’t rely on logic, don’t rely on inference, don’t go by reasoned contemplation, don’t go by the acceptance of a view after consideration, don’t go by the appearance of competence, and don’t think ‘The ascetic is our respected teacher.’ "

msgctxt "an3.65:26.2"
msgid "Yadā tumhe, kālāmā, attanāva jāneyyātha: "
msgstr "But when you know for yourselves: "

msgctxt "an3.65:26.3"
msgid "‘ime dhammā kusalā, ime dhammā anavajjā, ime dhammā viññuppasatthā, ime dhammā samattā samādinnā hitāya sukhāya saṃvattantī’ti, atha tumhe, kālāmā, upasampajja vihareyyātha. "
msgstr "‘These things are skillful, blameless, praised by sensible people, and when you undertake them, they lead to welfare and happiness’, then you should acquire them and keep them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc27
msgctxt "an3.65:27.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, kālāmā, "
msgstr "What do you think, Kālāmas? "

msgctxt "an3.65:27.2"
msgid "alobho purisassa ajjhattaṃ uppajjamāno uppajjati hitāya vā ahitāya vā”ti? "
msgstr "Does contentment come up in a person for their welfare or harm?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc28
msgctxt "an3.65:28.1"
msgid "“Hitāya, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Welfare, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.191, sc29
msgctxt "an3.65:29.1"
msgid "“Aluddho panāyaṃ, kālāmā, purisapuggalo lobhena anabhibhūto apariyādinnacitto neva pāṇaṃ hanati, na adinnaṃ ādiyati, na paradāraṃ gacchati, na musā bhaṇati, na parampi tathattāya samādapeti, yaṃ sa hoti dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti. "
msgstr "“An individual who is content, not overcome by greed, doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit adultery, lie, or encourage others to do the same. Is that for their lasting welfare and happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc30
msgctxt "an3.65:30.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc31
msgctxt "an3.65:31.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, kālāmā, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Kālāmas? "

msgctxt "an3.65:31.2"
msgid "adoso purisassa ajjhattaṃ uppajjamāno uppajjati … pe … "
msgstr "Does love come up in a person for their welfare or harm? … "

msgctxt "an3.65:31.3"
msgid "amoho purisassa ajjhattaṃ uppajjamāno uppajjati … pe … "
msgstr "Does understanding come up in a person for their welfare or harm? … "

msgctxt "an3.65:31.4"
msgid "hitāya sukhāyā”ti. "
msgstr "Is that for their lasting welfare and happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc32
msgctxt "an3.65:32.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc33
msgctxt "an3.65:33.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, kālāmā, ime dhammā kusalā vā akusalā vā”ti? "
msgstr "“What do you think, Kālāmas, are these things skillful or unskillful?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc34
msgctxt "an3.65:34.1"
msgid "“Kusalā, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Skillful, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc35
msgctxt "an3.65:35.1"
msgid "“Sāvajjā vā anavajjā vā”ti? "
msgstr "“Blameworthy or blameless?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc36
msgctxt "an3.65:36.1"
msgid "“Anavajjā, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Blameless, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc37
msgctxt "an3.65:37.1"
msgid "“Viññugarahitā vā viññuppasatthā vā”ti? "
msgstr "“Criticized or praised by sensible people?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc38
msgctxt "an3.65:38.1"
msgid "“Viññuppasatthā, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Praised by sensible people, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc39
msgctxt "an3.65:39.1"
msgid "“Samattā samādinnā hitāya sukhāya saṃvattanti no vā? "
msgstr "“When you undertake them, do they lead to welfare and happiness, or not? "

msgctxt "an3.65:39.2"
msgid "Kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti? "
msgstr "Or how do you see this?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc40
msgctxt "an3.65:40.1"
msgid "“Samattā, bhante, samādinnā hitāya sukhāya saṃvattanti. "
msgstr "“When you undertake them, they lead to welfare and happiness. "

msgctxt "an3.65:40.2"
msgid "Evaṃ no ettha hotī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how we see it.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.192, sc41
msgctxt "an3.65:41.1"
msgid "“Iti kho, kālāmā, yaṃ taṃ avocumhā: "
msgstr "“So, Kālāmas, when I said: "

msgctxt "an3.65:41.2"
msgid "‘etha tumhe, kālāmā. "
msgstr "‘Please, "

msgctxt "an3.65:41.3"
msgid "Mā anussavena, mā paramparāya, mā itikirāya, mā piṭakasampadānena, mā takkahetu, mā nayahetu, mā ākāraparivitakkena, mā diṭṭhinijjhānakkhantiyā, mā bhabbarūpatāya, mā samaṇo no garūti. "
msgstr "don’t go by oral transmission, don’t go by lineage, don’t go by testament, don’t go by canonical authority, don’t rely on logic, don’t rely on inference, don’t go by reasoned contemplation, don’t go by the acceptance of a view after consideration, don’t go by the appearance of competence, and don’t think “The ascetic is our respected teacher.” "

msgctxt "an3.65:41.4"
msgid "Yadā tumhe, kālāmā, attanāva jāneyyātha—"
msgstr "But when you know for yourselves: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.65:41.5"
msgid "ime dhammā kusalā, ime dhammā anavajjā, ime dhammā viññuppasatthā, ime dhammā samattā samādinnā hitāya sukhāya saṃvattantīti, atha tumhe, kālāmā, upasampajja vihareyyāthā’ti, "
msgstr "“These things are skillful, blameless, praised by sensible people, and when you undertake them, they lead to welfare and happiness”, then you should acquire them and keep them.’ "

msgctxt "an3.65:41.6"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc42
#. VAR: Sa kho so → yo kho (mr)
#. VAR: patissato → sato (mr)
msgctxt "an3.65:42.1"
msgid "Sa kho so, kālāmā, ariyasāvako evaṃ vigatābhijjho vigatabyāpādo asammūḷho sampajāno patissato mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ, iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjhena pharitvā viharati. "
msgstr "Then that noble disciple is rid of desire, rid of ill will, unconfused, aware, and mindful. They meditate spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.65:42.2"
msgid "Karuṇāsahagatena cetasā … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate spreading a heart full of compassion to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of compassion to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.65:42.3"
msgid "muditāsahagatena cetasā … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate spreading a heart full of rejoicing to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of rejoicing to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.65:42.4"
msgid "upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ, iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjhena pharitvā viharati. "
msgstr "They meditate spreading a heart full of equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc43
#. VAR: Sa → sace (mr)
msgctxt "an3.65:43.1"
msgid "Sa kho so, kālāmā, ariyasāvako evaṃ averacitto evaṃ abyāpajjhacitto evaṃ asaṃkiliṭṭhacitto evaṃ visuddhacitto. "
msgstr "When that noble disciple has a mind that’s free of enmity and ill will, uncorrupted and purified, "

msgctxt "an3.65:43.2"
msgid "Tassa diṭṭheva dhamme cattāro assāsā adhigatā honti. "
msgstr "they’ve won four consolations in the present life. "

#. VAR: sukatadukkaṭānaṃ → sukaṭadukkaṭānaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: athāhaṃ → ṭhānamahaṃ (bj, pts1) | ṭhānametaṃ yenāhaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an3.65:43.3"
msgid "‘Sace kho pana atthi paro loko, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko, athāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissāmī’ti, ayamassa paṭhamo assāso adhigato hoti. "
msgstr "‘If it turns out there is another world, and good and bad deeds have a result, then—when the body breaks up, after death—I’ll be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.’ This is the first consolation they’ve won. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc44
#. VAR: athāhaṃ → idhāhaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: sukhiṃ → sukhaṃ (bj) | sukhī (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an3.65:44.1"
msgid "‘Sace kho pana natthi paro loko, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko, athāhaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme averaṃ abyāpajjhaṃ anīghaṃ sukhiṃ attānaṃ pariharāmī’ti, ayamassa dutiyo assāso adhigato hoti. "
msgstr "‘If it turns out there is no other world, and good and bad deeds don’t have a result, then in the present life I’ll keep myself free of enmity and ill will, untroubled and happy.’ This is the second consolation they’ve won. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc45
msgctxt "an3.65:45.1"
msgid "‘Sace kho pana karoto karīyati pāpaṃ, na kho panāhaṃ kassaci pāpaṃ cetemi. "
msgstr "‘If it turns out that bad things happen to people who do bad things, then since I have no bad intentions, "

msgctxt "an3.65:45.2"
msgid "Akarontaṃ kho pana maṃ pāpakammaṃ kuto dukkhaṃ phusissatī’ti, ayamassa tatiyo assāso adhigato hoti. "
msgstr "and since I’m not doing anything bad, how can suffering touch me?’ This is the third consolation they’ve won. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc46
msgctxt "an3.65:46.1"
msgid "‘Sace kho pana karoto na karīyati pāpaṃ, athāhaṃ ubhayeneva visuddhaṃ attānaṃ samanupassāmī’ti, ayamassa catuttho assāso adhigato hoti. "
msgstr "‘If it turns out that bad things don’t happen to people who do bad things, then I still see myself pure on both sides.’ This is the fourth consolation they’ve won. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc47
msgctxt "an3.65:47.1"
msgid "Sa kho so, kālāmā, ariyasāvako evaṃ averacitto evaṃ abyāpajjhacitto evaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhacitto evaṃ visuddhacitto. "
msgstr "When that noble disciple has a mind that’s free of enmity and ill will, undefiled and purified, "

msgctxt "an3.65:47.2"
msgid "Tassa diṭṭheva dhamme ime cattāro assāsā adhigatā hontī”ti. "
msgstr "they’ve won these four consolations in the present life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.193, sc48
msgctxt "an3.65:48.1"
msgid "“Evametaṃ, bhagavā, evametaṃ, sugata. "
msgstr "“That’s so true, Blessed One! That’s so true, Holy One! "

msgctxt "an3.65:48.2"
msgid "Sa kho so, bhante, ariyasāvako evaṃ averacitto evaṃ abyāpajjhacitto evaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhacitto evaṃ visuddhacitto. "
msgstr "When that noble disciple has a mind that’s free of enmity and ill will, undefiled and purified, "

msgctxt "an3.65:48.3"
msgid "Tassa diṭṭheva dhamme cattāro assāsā adhigatā honti. "
msgstr "they’ve won these four consolations in the present life. … "

msgctxt "an3.65:48.4"
msgid "‘Sace kho pana atthi paro loko, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko, athāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissāmī’ti, ayamassa paṭhamo assāso adhigato hoti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc49
msgctxt "an3.65:49.1"
msgid "‘Sace kho pana natthi paro loko, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko, athāhaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme averaṃ abyāpajjhaṃ anīghaṃ sukhiṃ attānaṃ pariharāmī’ti, ayamassa dutiyo assāso adhigato hoti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc50
msgctxt "an3.65:50.1"
msgid "‘Sace kho pana karoto karīyati pāpaṃ, na kho panāhaṃ kassaci pāpaṃ cetemi, akarontaṃ kho pana maṃ pāpakammaṃ kuto dukkhaṃ phusissatī’ti, ayamassa tatiyo assāso adhigato hoti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc51
msgctxt "an3.65:51.1"
msgid "‘Sace kho pana karoto na karīyati pāpaṃ, athāhaṃ ubhayeneva visuddhaṃ attānaṃ samanupassāmī’ti, ayamassa catuttho assāso adhigato hoti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc52
msgctxt "an3.65:52.1"
msgid "Sa kho so, bhante, ariyasāvako evaṃ averacitto evaṃ abyāpajjhacitto evaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhacitto evaṃ visuddhacitto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.65:52.2"
msgid "Tassa diṭṭheva dhamme ime cattāro assāsā adhigatā honti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc53
msgctxt "an3.65:53.1"
msgid "Abhikkantaṃ, bhante … pe … "
msgstr "Excellent, sir! Excellent! … "

msgctxt "an3.65:53.2"
msgid "ete mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca. "
msgstr "We go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "an3.65:53.3"
msgid "Upāsake no, bhante, bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupete saraṇaṃ gate”ti. "
msgstr "From this day forth, may the Buddha remember us as lay followers who have gone for refuge for life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.65:53.4"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

